And again, this seems to be literal here, doesn't it?

23:36.368 --> 23:39.552
Because it's talking about they're watching a great city burning.

23:40.313 --> 23:45.118
So if it's just a system, this language here is too figurative.

23:45.138 --> 23:46.660
It would be too figurative.

23:46.680 --> 23:48.882
It needs to be understood as literal, kings of the earth.

23:49.283 --> 23:56.210
They're mourning the fact that their commercial industry is collapsing because God is bringing it down.

23:56.866 --> 24:05.414
Verse 10, standing at a distance for fear of her torment, saying, alas, alas, that great city, Babylon, that mighty city, for in one hour your judgment has come.

24:05.735 --> 24:16.105
Verse 11, and the merchants of the earth, in addition to the kings, will weep and mourn over her, for no one buys their merchandise anymore.

24:16.125 --> 24:25.234
See, it has this domino effect in commercial industry, and there's going to be a list now here in verse 12, a list of assets and commodities.

24:26.114 --> 24:49.298
So verse 12, merchandise of gold and silver, precious stones and pearls, fine linen and purple, silk and scarlet, every kind of citron wood, every kind of object of ivory, every kind of object of most precious wood, bronze, iron and marble, and cinnamon and incense, frankincense, rather fragrant oil and frankincense, wine and oil,

24:49.570 --> 24:56.500
fine flower and wheat, cattle and sheep, horses and chariots and bodies and souls of men.

24:57.000 --> 25:06.874
The fruit that you're so longed for has gone from you and all the things which are rich and splendid have gone from you and you shall find them no more at all.

25:06.934 --> 25:12.542
And so it's a list of all this different, these commercial commodities and assets.

25:12.722 --> 25:16.908
These are the things that are just going to begin to lose their value.

25:17.008 --> 25:18.130
It's going to become

25:18.274 --> 25:20.477
You know, you talk about a stock market crash.

25:20.537 --> 25:22.680
I mean, all of this is going to come to an end.

25:23.661 --> 25:31.452
Verse 15, the merchants of these things who became rich by her will stand at a distance for fear of her torment, weeping and wailing.

25:31.472 --> 25:32.634
There you have these words again.

25:33.214 --> 25:45.231
And saying, alas, alas, that great city that was clothed in fine linen, purple and scarlet and adorned with golden precious stones and pearls for in one hour, such great riches came to nothing.

25:46.373 --> 25:47.474
Every ship master.

25:47.874 --> 26:02.622
For some of your translations say, Captain, every captain, all who traveled by ship, sailors, and as many as trade on the sea stood at a distance and cried out when they saw the smoke of her burning saying, what is like this great city?

26:03.704 --> 26:11.218
And verse 19, they threw dust on their heads and cried out weeping and wailing and saying,

26:11.906 --> 26:14.209
very similar to what the merchants and the kings said.

26:14.309 --> 26:24.924
Alas, alas, that great city in which all who had ships on the sea became rich by her wealth for in one hour she is made desolate.

26:25.024 --> 26:31.092
And so between all these different verses here, verses 9, 11, and 19, it talks about kings.

26:31.132 --> 26:32.254
It talks about merchants.

26:32.294 --> 26:33.916
It talks about captains and sailors.

26:34.397 --> 26:35.378
They will weep.

26:35.842 --> 26:37.524
It talks about they will lament.

26:37.604 --> 26:43.069
It says they will mourn and they will wail because they will lament their material loss.

26:43.109 --> 26:47.373
But what is so sad is they're not lamenting about their spiritual loss.

26:47.393 --> 26:51.037
They're not lamenting over the fact that they are estranged from God.

26:51.657 --> 26:53.659
This is not moving them to the heart of God.

26:54.040 --> 27:02.848
They are lamenting over the fact that their material things have lost their value or disintegrated or burned or been taken from them.

27:03.209 --> 27:04.530
That's what they're mourning about.

27:04.706 --> 27:06.449
They're weeping over their stuff.

27:07.190 --> 27:11.296
I mean, you talk about a culture that's become consumed with materialism.

27:11.737 --> 27:12.859
It's this culture here.

27:13.780 --> 27:17.867
And God is going to bring it to an end because God knocks down every idol in our lives.

27:18.968 --> 27:21.572
At some point by some means or some methods.

27:21.612 --> 27:22.414
Have you ever noticed that?

27:22.754 --> 27:29.505
When you start to have too much affection for something or someone other than God, you ever noticed how he begins to knock down our idols?

27:30.446 --> 27:32.850
And so God is the only one who should be exalted.

27:33.314 --> 27:42.083
The whole world is gonna turn towards this religious system, God will destroy, and the whole world is gonna turn towards this commercial economic system that they worship.

27:42.804 --> 27:43.885
God's gonna destroy it.

27:44.666 --> 27:48.530
He's gonna show them on whom they should have their true dependence.

27:49.531 --> 27:51.292
And so all of these things are gonna pass away.

27:51.352 --> 28:00.722
Now notice verse 20, rejoice over her O heaven, and you holy apostles and prophets, for God has avenged you

28:00.834 --> 28:01.615
on her.

28:01.735 --> 28:02.897
Notice what's happening in heaven.

28:03.117 --> 28:10.065
There's rejoicing in heaven while there is mourning and weeping and wailing going on on earth.

28:10.185 --> 28:11.087
Quite a contrast.

28:12.328 --> 28:30.290
The last section here in verse 21 says, then a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone and threw it into the sea saying, thus with violence the great city Babylon shall be thrown down and shall not be found

28:30.434 --> 28:31.035
anymore.

28:31.836 --> 28:41.106
So the last verse to highlight from this chapter is verse 21 here where he says just what I read and it's telling us that God will destroy Babylon.

28:41.947 --> 28:46.031
Will he destroy the city or will he destroy the system or both?

28:47.172 --> 28:47.853
I think it's both.

28:48.594 --> 28:59.666
It's both this economic center that also is a system that people have been exalting and God is going to destroy it.

29:00.290 --> 29:01.372
They won't be found anymore.

29:01.872 --> 29:10.285
Verse 22, the sound of harpists, musicians, flutists, or flautists, and trumpeters shall not be heard in you anymore.

29:10.305 --> 29:14.031
No craftsmen of any craft shall be found in you anymore.

29:14.832 --> 29:17.756
And the sound of a millstone shall not be heard in you anymore.

29:18.577 --> 29:21.782
The light of a lamp shall not shine in you anymore.

29:22.623 --> 29:27.090
And the voice of bridegroom and bride shall not be heard in you anymore.

29:27.682 --> 29:42.940
for your merchants were the great men of the earth, for by your sorcery all the nations were deceived, and in her was found in the blood of prophets and saints, and of all who were slain on the earth."

29:44.221 --> 29:51.490
And so God brings an end to spiritual Babylon and political commercial Babylon.

29:51.950 --> 29:55.154
And Paul will tell us in 2 Thessalonians 2.8,

29:55.874 --> 30:00.320
that the lawless one, that is the antichrist, because all of this rises on the back of the antichrist.

30:01.222 --> 30:13.299
Paul writes in 2 Thessalonians 2, 8, that the lawless one will be overthrown by the breath of the Lord and will be destroyed by the splendor of his coming.

30:14.901 --> 30:18.266
That's chapter 19, and that's next week.

30:18.646 --> 30:21.150
So read ahead, we'll pick it up there next week.

30:21.971 --> 30:23.954
Lord, thank you for this time and your word.

30:25.314 --> 30:30.960
And thank you for a reminder to us that we can't get caught up in materialism.

30:31.760 --> 30:41.650
Help us to be good stewards of what you've entrusted to us, whether it is much or whether it is little, that we might use all that you've given us for your glory and for your honor.

30:42.891 --> 30:45.154
Help us not to be greedy or covetous, Lord.

30:45.174 --> 30:53.522
We know our hearts are prone to those things, so we pray God that you would regularly remind us that you own everything.

30:54.402 --> 31:01.356
We're just managers of it, and we thank you that you've entrusted to us and given to us all that we have.

31:02.438 --> 31:03.901
We're grateful, Lord, we're thankful.

31:04.261 --> 31:07.187
May we be good stewards of it for your glory in Jesus' name.

31:08.469 --> 31:10.834
And everybody said amen.

